<section.body>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|3|32:3">
<para.text>
For federal income tax purposes, cooperatives are classified either as exempt farmers' cooperatives or nonexempt cooperatives. An &ldquo;“exempt farmers' cooperative&rdquo;” is an association of farmers, fruit growers, or the like, organized and operated on a cooperative basis for the purpose of marketing the products of members or other producers and turning back to them the proceeds of sales, less the necessary marketing expenses, on the basis of either the quantity or the value of the products furnished by them; or purchasing supplies and equipment for the use of members or other persons and turning over such supplies and equipment to them at actual cost plus necessary expenses.<footnote><footnote.reference>14</footnote.reference><footnote.body>1►<f_field>fn.fnref="1"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|3|32:3"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GEN"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§521(b)(1).Research ReferencesAgricultural and horticultural organizations, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04A9JJ"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d  &pp;D-4700 to D-4705.Cooperatives, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04D2OF"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d  &pp;E-1000 to E-1150.Farmers' cooperatives, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I047GEP"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &ss;§§5:176 to 5:1920.</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|3|32:3">
<para.text>
A &ldquo;“nonexempt cooperative&rdquo;” can be defined as one that does not meet the requirements of an exempt farmers' cooperative either because it engages in occupations dissimilar to those of farmers, fruit growers, and the like<footnote><footnote.reference>15</footnote.reference><footnote.body>2►<f_field>fn.fnref="2"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|3|32:3"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04A9JL"</f_field>26 C.F.R. &s;§1.521-1(d).Research ReferencesWhat cooperative exemption means, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04D2OH"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1002.Nonexempt farmers cooperatives, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04FVTD"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &ss;§§5:16 to 5:185:17 to 5:19.</footnote.body></footnote> or because it fails to satisfy some other requirement.<footnote><footnote.reference>16</footnote.reference><footnote.body>3►<f_field>fn.fnref="3"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|3|32:3"</f_field>See, generally, ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GER"</f_field>26 C.F.R. &s;§1.521-1.</footnote.body></footnote> Most other cooperative corporations are generally taxable as ordinary business corporations, except that they may exclude from their income earnings distributed as patronage dividends.<footnote><footnote.reference>17</footnote.reference><footnote.body>4►<f_field>fn.fnref="4"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|3|32:3"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GFX"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &ss;§§1381(a), 1382(b).Research ReferencesFor general discussion of taxation of cooperatives, see ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04D2PP"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &ss;§§5:176 to 5:2019 and ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04FVUL"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d  &pp;E-1000 to E-1045.</footnote.body></footnote> This chapter is concerned primarily with exempt farmers' cooperatives.
</para.text>
</para>
</section.body>
</section>
<analytical.level.body>
<section.block>
<section>
<section.front>
<outline.name.block>
<designator>32:4</designator>
<name>Tax consequences for exempt farmers' cooperative</name>
</outline.name.block>
<research.reference.block>
<reference.entry><ref.text>►<field>tk.ref.id="I047GFZ"</field>West's Key Number Digest, Internal Revenue &key;3985 to 3988</ref.text></reference.entry>
</research.reference.block>
</section.front>
<section.body>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4">
<para.text>
An &ldquo;“exempt farmers' cooperative&rdquo;” is subject to the general corporation income tax and the alternative tax on capital gains.<footnote><footnote.reference>18</footnote.reference><footnote.body>1►<f_field>fn.fnref="1"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04A9KV"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1381(b).►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>For the general corporation income tax, see ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GG2"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§11; for alternative tax on capital gains, see ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04A9KY"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1201.Research ReferencesHow cooperatives are taxed, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04D2PU"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1001.Taxation of farmers' cooperatives, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04FVUQ"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:176.</footnote.body></footnote> However, in determining taxable income, such organizations need not take into account amounts paid during the payment period for the taxable year: as certain patronage dividends;<footnote><footnote.reference>19</footnote.reference><footnote.body>2►<f_field>fn.fnref="2"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>See ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GLP"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(b)(1).Research References►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04A9QL"</f_field>Co-operative associations: rights in equity credits or patronage dividends, 50 A.L.R.3d 435.Co-op's deduction of patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04D2VH"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1101.Noncash patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04FW0D"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:187.</footnote.body></footnote> in money or other property (except written notices of allocation) in redemption of certain nonqualified written notices of allocation;<footnote><footnote.reference>20</footnote.reference><footnote.body>3►<f_field>fn.fnref="3"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>See ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05S4S0"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(b)(2).►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>For a definition of &ldquo;“written notice of allocation&rdquo;” and discussion of qualified and unqualified notices, see ►<f_field>x.ref.id="I05PBN4"</f_field>&s;§32:6.</footnote.body></footnote> as certain per-unit retain allocations;<footnote><footnote.reference>21</footnote.reference><footnote.body>4►<f_field>fn.fnref="4"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>See ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05MII8"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(b)(3).Research ReferencesCo-op's deduction of per-unit retain allocations, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05JPDC"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1101.</footnote.body></footnote> or in money or other property (except per-unit retain certificates) in redemption of certain nonqualified per-unit retain certificates.<footnote><footnote.reference>22</footnote.reference><footnote.body>5►<f_field>fn.fnref="5"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>See ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05S4RY"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(b)(4).</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4">
<para.text>
The &ldquo;“patronage dividend&rdquo;” is an amount paid to a patron by a Section 1381 organization on the basis of quantity or value of business done with or for such patron; under an obligation of such organization to pay such amount, which obligation existed before the organization received the amount so paid; and that is determined by reference to the net earnings of the organization from business done with or for its patrons.<footnote><footnote.reference>23</footnote.reference><footnote.body>6►<f_field>fn.fnref="6"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05PBN2"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(a).Research ReferencesWhat is patronage dividend, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05MII6"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d  &p;E-1104.Noncash patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05JPDA"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:187.</footnote.body></footnote> The payment period for any taxable year is the period beginning with the first day of such taxable year and ending with the fifteenth day of the ninth month following the close of such year.<footnote><footnote.reference>24</footnote.reference><footnote.body>7►<f_field>fn.fnref="7"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05S4RW"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(d).</footnote.body></footnote> &ldquo;“Per-unit retain allocation&rdquo;” means any allocation, by an exempt cooperative, to a patron with respect to products marketed for such patron, the amount of which is fixed without reference to the net earnings of the organization pursuant to an agreement between the organization and the patron.<footnote><footnote.reference>25</footnote.reference><footnote.body>8►<f_field>fn.fnref="8"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05S4QQ"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(f).Research References&ldquo;“Per-unit retain allocation&rdquo;” defined, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05PBLU"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1126.</footnote.body></footnote> &ldquo;“Per-unit retain certificate&rdquo;” means any written notice that discloses to the recipient the stated dollar amount of a per-unit retain allocation to such recipient by the organization.<footnote><footnote.reference>26</footnote.reference><footnote.body>9►<f_field>fn.fnref="9"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05MIGY"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(g).</footnote.body></footnote> A &ldquo;“qualified per-unit retain certificate&rdquo;” is any per-unit retain certificate that the distributee has agreed, in a specified manner, to take into account at its stated dollar amount as provided in ►<field>st.ref.id="I05JPC2"</field>Section 1385(a) of the Internal Revenue Code.1<footnote><footnote.reference>27</footnote.reference><footnote.body>10►<f_field>fn.fnref="10"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05S4QO"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(h).</footnote.body></footnote> &ldquo;“Nonqualified per-unit retain certificate&rdquo;” means a per-unit retain certificate that does not meet the requirements of a qualified per-unit retain certificate.1<footnote><footnote.reference>28</footnote.reference><footnote.body>11►<f_field>fn.fnref="11"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05PBLS"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(i).</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4">
<para.text>
In addition, the organization may deduct amounts paid during the taxable year as dividends on its capital stock,1<footnote><footnote.reference>29</footnote.reference><footnote.body>12►<f_field>fn.fnref="12"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>See ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05MIGW"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(c)(1).Research ReferencesCo-op's deduction of patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05S4L0"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1101.Noncash patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05PBG4"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:187.</footnote.body></footnote> as well as amounts paid during the payment period for the taxable year in money, qualified written notices of allocation, or other property (except nonqualified written notices of allocation) on a patronage basis to patrons with respect to the organization's earnings during such taxable year that were derived from business done for the United States or any of its agencies or from sources other than patronage.1<footnote><footnote.reference>30</footnote.reference><footnote.body>13►<f_field>fn.fnref="13"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05MIB8"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(c)(2)(A).</footnote.body></footnote> It may also deduct amounts paid during the payment period for the taxable year in money or other property (except written notices of allocation) in redemption of a nonqualified written notice of allocation which was paid, during the payment period for the taxable year during which the earnings were derived, on a patronage basis to a patron with respect to earnings derived from business done for the United States or for any of its agencies or from sources other than patronage.1<footnote><footnote.reference>31</footnote.reference><footnote.body>14►<f_field>fn.fnref="14"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GSU"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(c)(2)(B).</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4">
<para.text>
The amount of any patronage dividend that is paid in money, a qualified written notice of allocation, or other property (except a nonqualified written notice of allocation) and that is received by the patron during the taxable year from an exempt farmer's cooperative must be included in gross income.1<footnote><footnote.reference>32</footnote.reference><footnote.body>15►<f_field>fn.fnref="15"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04A9XQ"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1385(a)(1); ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GSX"</f_field>26 C.F.R. &s;§1.1385-1(a).</footnote.body></footnote> However, such amount, to the extent that it is properly taken into account as an adjustment to basis of property or is attributable to personal, living, or family items is not includable.1<footnote><footnote.reference>33</footnote.reference><footnote.body>16►<f_field>fn.fnref="16"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04A9XT"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1385(b).</footnote.body></footnote> In addition, includable in the patron's gross income are nonpatronage distributions by tax-exempt farmers' cooperatives paid in money, qualified written notices of allocation, or other property except nonqualified written notices of allocation, received by the patron during the taxable year from such a cooperative,1<footnote><footnote.reference>34</footnote.reference><footnote.body>17►<f_field>fn.fnref="17"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04D32P"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1385(a)(2).</footnote.body></footnote> and the amount of any per-unit retain allocation which is paid in qualified per-unit retain certificates and received by the patron during the taxable year from a tax-exempt farmers' cooperative or other specified cooperative.1<footnote><footnote.reference>35</footnote.reference><footnote.body>18►<f_field>fn.fnref="18"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GSZ"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1385(a)(3).</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4">
<para.text>
An organization claiming exemption must file IRS Form 1028 with the district director for the internal revenue district in which the organization's principal place of business or principal office is located.1<footnote><footnote.reference>36</footnote.reference><footnote.body>19►<f_field>fn.fnref="19"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|4|32:4"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04A9XV"</f_field>26 C.F.R. &s;§1.521-1(e).Research ReferencesApplying for exemption, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04D32R"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1043.Exempt farmers' cooperatives, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04FW7N"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:2019.</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
</section.body>
</section>
<analytical.level.body>
<section.block>
<section>
<section.front>
<outline.name.block>
<designator>32:5</designator>
<name>Tax consequences for nonexempt cooperative</name>
</outline.name.block>
<research.reference.block>
<reference.entry><ref.text>►<field>tk.ref.id="I047GU5"</field>West's Key Number Digest, Internal Revenue &key;3985 to 3988</ref.text></reference.entry>
</research.reference.block>
</section.front>
<section.body>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|5|32:5">
<para.text>
A nonexempt cooperative is treated in the same manner as an exempt farmers' cooperative for computation of taxable income, with the exception that a nonexempt cooperative is not entitled to the deductions allowable under ►<field>st.ref.id="I04A9Z1"</field>Section 1382(c) of the Internal Revenue Code.<footnote><footnote.reference>37</footnote.reference><footnote.body>1►<f_field>fn.fnref="1"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|5|32:5"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04D33X"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1382(c).►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|5|32:5"</f_field>For a discussion of such deductions as they relate to exempt farmers' cooperatives, see ►<f_field>x.ref.id="I04FW8T"</f_field>&s;§32:4.Research ReferencesHow cooperatives are taxed, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I047GU7"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1001.Farmers' cooperatives, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04A9Z3"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &ss;§§5:16 to 5:185:17 to 5:19.</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
</section.body>
</section>
<analytical.level.body>
<section.block>
<section>
<section.front>
<outline.name.block>
<designator>32:6</designator>
<name>Written notices of allocation</name>
</outline.name.block>
<research.reference.block>
<reference.entry><ref.text>►<field>tk.ref.id="I04D33Z"</field>West's Key Number Digest, Internal Revenue &key;3985</ref.text></reference.entry>
<reference.entry><ref.text>►<field>tk.ref.id="I047GU9"</field>West's Key Number Digest, Internal Revenue &key;3987</ref.text></reference.entry>
</research.reference.block>
</section.front>
<section.body>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6">
<para.text>
A &ldquo;“written notice of allocation&rdquo;” is notice in any capital stock, revolving fund certificate, retain certificate, certificate of indebtedness, letter of advice, or other written notice that discloses to the recipient the stated dollar amount allocated to the individual by the organization and the portion, if any, constituting a patronage dividend.<footnote><footnote.reference>38</footnote.reference><footnote.body>1►<f_field>fn.fnref="1"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GZX"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(b).Research References►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04AA4T"</f_field>Co-operative associations: rights in equity credits or patronage dividends, 50 A.L.R.3d 435.Qualified written notice of allocation, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04D39P"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1121.Noncash patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04FWEL"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:187.</footnote.body></footnote> Such notices are classified as either qualified or nonqualified.<footnote><footnote.reference>39</footnote.reference><footnote.body>2►<f_field>fn.fnref="2"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047GZZ"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(c), (d).</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6">
<para.text>
The &ldquo;“qualified written notice of allocation&rdquo;” means one that may be redeemed in cash at its stated dollar amount at any time within a period beginning on the date such written notice is paid and ending not earlier than 90 days from such date, but only if the distributee receives written notice of the right of redemption at the time of receipt of the written notice of allocation and a written notice of allocation that the distributee has consented to take into account at its stated dollar amount for purposes of computing the distributee's gross income.<footnote><footnote.reference>40</footnote.reference><footnote.body>3►<f_field>fn.fnref="3"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04D39R"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(c).</footnote.body></footnote> A qualified written notice of allocation does not include a written notice of allocation that is paid as part of the patronage dividend or as part of certain other payments unless 20&percnt;% or more of the amount is paid in money or by qualified check.<footnote><footnote.reference>41</footnote.reference><footnote.body>4►<f_field>fn.fnref="4"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04FWEN"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(c)(1).</footnote.body></footnote> A &ldquo;“qualified check&rdquo;” means only a check (or other instrument that is redeemable in money) that is paid as a part of a patronage dividend or as a part of certain other payments to a distributee who has not consented with respect to such patronage dividend or payment and on which there is clearly imprinted a statement that the endorsement and cashing of the check or other instrument constitutes the payee's consent to include in his or her gross income, as provided in the federal income tax laws, the stated dollar amount of the written notice of allocation that is part of the patronage dividend or payment of which such qualified check is also a part.<footnote><footnote.reference>42</footnote.reference><footnote.body>5►<f_field>fn.fnref="5"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I047H02"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(c)(4).Research ReferencesPatron's consent by qualified check to report written notice of allocation in income, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04AA4Y"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1130.Noncash patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04D39U"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:187.</footnote.body></footnote> A &ldquo;“qualified check&rdquo;” does not include any check or other instrument that is paid as part of a patronage dividend or payment that does not include a written notice of allocation (other than a written notice of allocation as described in Section 1388(c)(1)(A) of the Code).<footnote><footnote.reference>43</footnote.reference><footnote.body>6►<f_field>fn.fnref="6"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I04FWEQ"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(c)(4).Research ReferencesPatron's consent by qualified check to report written notice of allocation in income, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I047H04"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1130.Noncash patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I04AA50"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:187.</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6">
<para.text>
The distributee's consent may be obtained through the distributee's written consent;<footnote><footnote.reference>44</footnote.reference><footnote.body>7►<f_field>fn.fnref="7"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05S4CI"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(c)(2)(A).</footnote.body></footnote> the distributee's obtaining or retaining membership in the cooperative after the organization has adopted a bylaw providing that membership in the organization constitutes such consent and the distributee has received a written notification and copy of such bylaw;<footnote><footnote.reference>45</footnote.reference><footnote.body>8►<f_field>fn.fnref="8"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05PB7M"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(c)(2)(B) (requiring that such bylaw has been adopted after October 16, 1962).►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>For a bylaw provision providing that membership in a cooperative constitutes consent of the member to take allocations into income, see ►<f_field>x.ref.id="I05MI2Q"</f_field>&s;§32:30.Research ReferencesConsent of membership, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05S4CG"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1129.</footnote.body></footnote> or the distributee's endorsement and cashing of a qualified check, paid as part of the patronage dividend or payment of which such written notice of allocation is also a part, on or before the 90th day after the close of the payment period for the taxable year of the organization for which such patronage dividend or payment is paid.<footnote><footnote.reference>46</footnote.reference><footnote.body>9►<f_field>fn.fnref="9"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05PB7K"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(c)(2)(C).Research ReferencesPatron's consent by qualified check to report written notice of allocation in income, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05MI2O"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1130.Noncash patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05JOXS"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:187.</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6">
<para.text>
A &ldquo;“nonqualified written notice of allocation&rdquo;” is a written notice of allocation that is not described as a qualified written notice of allocation or a qualified check that is not cashed on or before the 90th day after the close of the payment period for the taxable year for which the distribution of which it is a part is paid.1<footnote><footnote.reference>47</footnote.reference><footnote.body>10►<f_field>fn.fnref="10"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|6|32:6"</f_field>►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05S46S"</f_field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(d).Research ReferencesNonqualified written notices of allocation, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05PB1W"</f_field>RIA Federal Tax Coordinator 2dFederal Tax Coordinator 2d &p;E-1122.Noncash patronage dividends, ►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05MHX0"</f_field>Federal Tax Guide to Legal Forms &s;§5:187.</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
