►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|7|32:7">
<para.text>
The New York tax upon and with respect to personal income<footnote><footnote.reference>48</footnote.reference><footnote.body>1►<f_field>fn.fnref="1"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|7|32:7"</f_field>See ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05MHWY"</f_field>NYTL &ss;§§601 et seq.</footnote.body></footnote> imposes a tax on the income of every resident individual of the state.<footnote><footnote.reference>49</footnote.reference><footnote.body>2►<f_field>fn.fnref="2"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|7|32:7"</f_field>See ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05JOS2"</f_field>NYTL &s;§601.</footnote.body></footnote> The term &ldquo;“resident individual&rdquo;” applies only to natural persons. Partnerships, as such, are not subject to this tax.<footnote><footnote.reference>50</footnote.reference><footnote.body>3►<f_field>fn.fnref="3"</f_field>►<f_field><para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|7|32:7"</f_field>See ►<f_field>st.ref.id="I05S46O"</f_field>NYTL &s;§605. For discussion of the federal tax provisions relating to agricultural cooperative associations, see <f_field>x.ref.id="I047H79"</f_field>&ss;§§32:3 et seq.Research References►<f_field>rc.ref.id="I05S46L"</f_field>State income tax treatment of partnerships and partners, 2 ALR 6th 1.</footnote.body></footnote>
</para.text>
</para>
<trace.deleted> ►p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|7|32:7"Each cooperative corporation organized, with or without capital stock, for the purpose of cooperative marketing of agricultural products, for the purpose of making loans to its members producing agricultural products, or for the purpose of purchasing food products for sale to its members, such a purchasing cooperative corporation having gross receipts from such sales of less than $500,000 in a calendar year, must pay to the State Commissioner of Taxation and Finance an annual fee of $10, in lieu of all franchise or license or corporation taxes.<footnote><footnote.reference>51</footnote.reference><footnote.body>4►fn.fnref="4"►p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|7|32:7"►st.ref.id="I05PB1P"Coop. Corp. Law &s;§77(1).</footnote.body></footnote> The annual fee is to be paid each year on the fifteenth day of March next succeeding the close of the calendar year.<footnote><footnote.reference>52</footnote.reference><footnote.body>5►fn.fnref="5"►p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|7|32:7"►st.ref.id="I05MHWT"Coop. Corp. Law &s;§77(3) with amendment ►st.ref.id="I05JORX"NY LEGIS 59 (2019), 2019 Sess. Law News of N.Y. Ch. 59 (S. 1509-C) stating: &ldquo;“Such annual fee shall be paid for each calendar year on the fifteenth day of March next succeeding the close of such calendar year but shall not be payable after January first, two thousand twenty; provided, however, that cooperative corporations described in subdivisions one or two of this section shall continue to not be subject to the franchise, license, and corporation taxes referenced in such subdivisions or, in the case of cooperative cooperations described in subdivision two of this section, the tax imposed under section one-hundred eighty-six-a of the tax law.&rdquo;”►<f_field>p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|7|32:7"</f_field>For discussion of the federal tax provisions relating to agricultural cooperative associations, see ►x.ref.id="I047H79"&ss;§§32:3 et seq.</footnote.body></footnote></trace.deleted>
