<section.body>
<online.view.item>FTR</online.view.item>
<online.view.item>COR</online.view.item>
<online.view.item>TEM</online.view.item>
<online.view.item>MTD</online.view.item>
►<field>form.du="0"</field><field>form.fid="Ia394e7c0181a11e68738d3db3a7c8dd3"</field>►<field>p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22"</field>No director of this cooperative shall be personally liable to this cooperative or its members for monetary damages for breach of fiduciary duty as a director, except for liability:
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>(a).
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22">
<para.text>
For a breach of the director's duty of loyalty to this cooperative or its members;
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>(b).
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22">
<para.text>
For acts or omissions not in good faith or that involve intentional misconduct or a knowing violation of law;
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>(c).
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22">
<para.text>
For a transaction from which the director derived an improper personal benefit; or
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>(d).
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22">
<para.text>
For an act or omission occurring prior to the date when the provisions of this Article (or predecessor thereto) became effective.
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22">
<para.text>
It is the intention of the members of this cooperative to eliminate or limit the personal liability of the directors of this cooperative to the greatest extent permitted under ►<field>st.ref.id="I048VKG"</field>Section 402(b) of the New York Business Corporation Law. If amendments to that section or other law are passed after the effective date of this Article, which authorize cooperatives to act to further limit or eliminate the personal liability of directors, then the liability of the directors of this cooperative shall be limited or eliminated to the greatest extent permitted by such statute as amended. Any repeal or modification of this Article by the members of this cooperative shall not adversely affect any right of or any protection available to a director of this cooperative that is in existence at the time of such repeal or modification.
</para.text>
</para>
<online.view.item>Notes to Form</online.view.item>
<trace.deleted>Drafter's Note</trace.deleted>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22">
<para.text>
<trace.deleted>Under the Section 5 of the New York Business Corporation Law, which applies to co-operative corporations, t</trace.deleted><trace>T</trace>he certificate of incorporation may set forth a provision eliminating or limiting the personal liability of directors to the corporation or its shareholders for damages for any breach of duty in such capacity, provided that no such provision shall eliminate or limit:
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22">
<para.text>
(1) the liability of any director if a judgment or other final adjudication adverse to him or her establishes that his or her acts or omissions were in bad faith or involved intentional misconduct or a knowing violation of law or that he or she personally gained in fact a financial profit or other advantage to which he or she was not legally entitled or that his or her acts violated Section 719 of the Business Corporation Law; or
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22">
<para.text>
(2) the liability of any director for any act or omission prior to the adoption of a provision authorized by this paragraph.<trace> </trace>
</para.text>
</para>
<trace.deleted> ►</trace.deleted><field>p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22"</field>See ►<field>st.ref.id="I048VKI"</field>BCL &s;§402(b)<trace>.</trace><trace.deleted> </trace.deleted><trace.deleted>and the following cases:</trace.deleted>
<trace.deleted> ►p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22"►cc.ref.id="I04BOPE"In re Ampal-American Israel Corp., 543 B.R. 464 (Bankr. S.D. N.Y. 2016) stating that exculpation clause in corporation's certificate of incorporation barred liability against corporation's independent directors for alleged violations of fiduciary duty in connection with approving excessive management and consulting fees.</trace.deleted>
<trace.deleted> ►p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22"►cc.ref.id="I04EHUA"Astarita v. Acme Bus Corp., 55 Misc. 3d 767, 52 N.Y.S.3d 616 (Sup 2017) stating that bus transportation corporation changed its principal place of business designated on its certificate of incorporation over 56 years earlier, by reporting that change on biennial registration statement filed with New York's Department of State, and thus, venue for personal injury suit against corporation was appropriately changed to county in which corporation had relocated its principal office as reported in biennial registration statement, even though corporation never filed any amendments to its certificate, where corporation's biennial registration statement updated information on its certificate and provided public with easily accessed current information.</trace.deleted>
<trace.deleted> ►p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|22|32:22"►cc.ref.id="I04HAZ6"Retirement Plan for General Employees of City of North Miami Beach v. McGraw, 158 A.D.3d 494, 71 N.Y.S.3d 27 (1st Dep't 2018) stating that corporation board of directors were not liable to shareholders, in derivative action, where certificate of incorporation contained an exculpatory provision.</trace.deleted>
