<trace.deleted>Drafter's Note</trace.deleted>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|24|32:24">
<para.text>
The officers of every cooperative corporation must include a president, one or more vice presidents, secretary, and treasurer who are required to be elected annually by the board of directors. The president and a first vice president must be members of the corporation or of a member corporation and must be elected from among the directors. Other officers need not be directors or members of the corporation. The offices of secretary and treasurer may be combined. ►<field>st.ref.id="I05KUM8"</field>Coop. Corp. Law &s;§64.
</para.text>
</para>
