<trace.deleted>Drafter's Note</trace.deleted>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|24|32:24">
<para.text>
For an agricultural cooperative corporation, the bylaws may provide for their amendment by the board of directors; however, any amendment adopted by the board that affects the preferential rights or obligations of the members or stockholders shall be reported to the next annual meeting of the corporation and, if not affirmatively approved thereat, shall cease to be in effect. Such bylaws reported to the annual meeting may be adopted, repealed, or amended on the affirmative vote of two-thirds of the members, stockholders, or delegates voting thereon at a meeting held after due written notice setting forth the proposed action and the purpose of the meeting. ►<field>st.ref.id="I05F8CG"</field>Coop. Corp. Law &s;§111.
</para.text>
</para>
