A corporation may provide a fair remuneration for its officers and directors and for members of its executive committee. No officer or director or member of the executive committee may be a party to a contract for profit with the corporation that in any way differs from similar contracts with members or with others or that varies from terms generally current in the district. ►<field>st.ref.id="I04HK3L"</field>Coop. Corp. Law &s;§62.
