<trace.deleted>Drafter's Note</trace.deleted>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|52|32:50">
<para.text>
As a contract of sale, the provisions of the New York Uniform Commercial Code would apply to the provisions concerning the place and time of delivery, the right of inspection, the effect of rejection, and the passage of title. ►<field>st.ref.id="I05PBN6"</field>NYUCC &ss;§§2-101 et seq.
</para.text>
</para>
