<para.text>
A corporation is given the right, in the event of a breach or threatened breach of a marketing contract by a member or by a contracting nonmember, to enjoin further breach of the contract and to obtain a decree of specific performance to enforce the contract. ►<field>st.ref.id="I09M44A"</field>Coop. Corp. Law &s;§70(3).
