<para.text>
The New York Uniform Commercial Code provides that in the case of sales, as in the case of contracts, generally, terms with respect to which the confirmatory memoranda of the parties agree or which are otherwise set forth in a writing intended by the parties as a final expression of their agreement with respect to such terms as are included therein may not be contradicted by evidence of any prior agreement or of a contemporaneous agreement. ►<field>st.ref.id="I04D2WX"</field>NYUCC &s;§2-202.
</para.text>
</para>
