<para.text>
A farmer's cooperative must limit the amount of business i<trace>t</trace><trace.deleted>f</trace.deleted> does with nonmembers. It may market products or purchase supplies and equipment for nonmembers only if: (i) the value does not exceed the value of the products, supplies, and equipment of members; and (ii) the value of the purchases made for those who are neither members nor producers does not exceed 15&percnt;% of total purchases. ►<field>st.ref.id="I04A9XW"</field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§521(b)(4). In addition, buying and selling for its own profit, such as selling by-products of purchases made for members to nonmembers, will disqualify a cooperative, even if sales are minimal.
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|53|32:51">
<para.text>
This explains the inclusion of a provision like that of Section 12 in the above agreement, which makes the contract itself an application for membership and an acceptance of that application.
</para.text>
</para>
