►<field>form.du="0"</field><field>form.fid="Ia39e5da0181a11e68738d3db3a7c8dd3"</field>►<field>p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53"</field>Agreement made [date of agreement], between [name of distributor], a distributor of dairy products having [his/her/its] principal office at [address of distributor], [name of city], [name of county], State of New York, referred to as &ldquo;“Distributor,&rdquo;” and [name of corporation], a cooperative corporation organized and existing under the laws of the State of New York, referred to as &ldquo;“Corporation.&rdquo;”
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>1. PURCHASE OF DAIRY PRODUCTS
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
Distributor agrees to buy [his/her/its] entire supply of [description of products], excluding [list of exclusions], from or through corporation, and corporation agrees to supply Distributor with all such products during the period and on the terms and conditions stated in this agreement.
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
Distributor may select from among the members of corporation those members whose products [he/she] desires to buy under this contract. Subject to the prior consent and approval of the board of directors of corporation, the selected members may then deliver such products directly to Distributor.
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>2. PRICES
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
Distributor shall pay to corporation for all dairy products sold and delivered to [him/her] by or through corporation not less than the minimum class prices set forth in the marketing agreement and order for the [name of marketing area] marketing area, State of New York, which [OPTIONAL: agreement was approved by [name of approver] and] became effective [effective date of agreement], and all amendments thereto. A copy of that marketing agreement and order is attached and made a part of this contract. Any new marketing order or amendment to the present order that affects this contract will become effective as to this contract when such new agreement or amendment becomes effective. If the present marketing agreement and order is terminated and not immediately replaced by a new agreement and order, the price to be paid for dairy products sold and delivered under this contract will be mutually agreed on between the parties to this contract.
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>3. INABILITY TO PERFORM
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
In case of any cause beyond the control of either party that shall render it impossible for corporation to deliver or Distributor to handle or dispose of dairy products to be sold or received under this agreement, no liability for nonperformance of this agreement caused hereby will be incurred during the existence of that cause. In the case of a short supply of the dairy products covered by this agreement, corporation agrees to prorate its production on a percentage of sales basis with every buyer of dairy products. In the case of its inabilities to supply dairy products from locally purchased sources, corporation will attempt to purchase such products for Distributor's account from outside sources.
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>4. ACCOUNTS, RECORDS, AND INSPECTIONS
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
Distributor agrees to keep complete and accurate records and accounts of all dairy products received by [him/her] or at [his/her/its] plant during the term of this agreement, showing the source, quality, quantity, and disposition thereof, with dates, together with accurate summaries thereof, and to render such accounts and records to corporation at the time of or prior to the settlement of accounts between the parties. Corporation will have full opportunity to check the sufficiency and accuracy of such records, accounts, and summaries and shall be permitted to have one or more representatives on the premises of Distributor where such dairy products are received, handled, processed, and prepared for sale and delivery at all times, with authority to take inventories; to examine the salespersons' daily load and return sheets and all other records and memoranda covering road sales; to check samples of cream; and to take samples of milk and cream from any cans or containers on the premises.
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>5. BUTTERFAT TESTS
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
The payment for all milk will be based on the average of not less than [number of separate butterfat tests] separate butterfat tests of each producer's delivery during each month, conducted by an independent laboratory acceptable to Distributor and corporation. Corporation and Distributor will each pay one-half of the cost of such tests. Both Distributor and corporation agree to accept as final the average of the [number of samples] samples taken by the laboratory as a basis of settlement. Corporation may check weights and butterfat tests at Distributor's plant at all times.
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>6. ACCOUNTING AND PAYMENT
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
Distributor will render to corporation not later than the [ordinal number of day] day of each month an accounting of all dairy products purchased during the preceding month. Payment for all such dairy products will be made directly to corporation daily on estimates furnished by corporation, subject to adjustment based on complete billing at the end of the month. Any underpayment or overpayment resulting from such daily payments as compared to the total billing for the month will be made good by the party liable therefor immediately on notice of such liability. Final adjustment as a result of ordered adjustment of receipts at sale shall be settled immediately on determination of the ordered adjustment.
</para.text>
</para>
►<field>fi.lvl="1"</field>7. EFFECTIVE DATE AND DURATION
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
This agreement will become effective on [effective date of agreement] and shall continue until terminated by either party on [number of days]-days written notice of cancellation.
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|55|32:53">
<para.text>
In witness, the parties have executed this agreement at [place of execution] the day and year first written above.
</para.text>
</para>
