►<field>form.du="0"</field><field>form.fid="Ia39f9620181a11e68738d3db3a7c8dd3"</field>►<field>p.ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|62|32:59"</field>Corporation agrees to resell such products of producer as may be pooled, together with products of like quality, grade, and classification delivered by other growers under substantially similar contracts, at the best prices obtainable under market conditions and to pay over the net amount received therefrom as payment in full to producer and producers named in contracts substantially similar to this agreement, according to the value of the products delivered by each producer after deducting therefrom the cost of receiving, handling, packing, manufacturing, storing, depreciation, advertising, and marketing and an investment charge not to exceed [percentage of gross resale proceeds]&percnt;% of the gross resale proceeds. From this charge, a commercial reserve may be created and deductions made for the creation of the capital funds of corporation, provided for by the bylaws thereof. The annual surplus from any deductions made by corporation and not prorated to any specific fund must be prorated among the producers delivering products in that year on the basis of their respective deliveries.
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|62|32:59">
<para.text>
Corporation agrees to pay an advance payment on the products as substantial as the market and financial conditions will permit, as determined by the board of directors in each season. Such payment will be made as soon as practicable after delivery of the products to corporation. Such advance payment may be proportionately higher for products classified in the more desirable grades or sizes from a commercial standpoint.
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|62|32:59">
<para.text>
Payment on each pool will be made from time to time, as rapidly as possible, in due proportion, until the accounts of each pool of the season are completely settled.
</para.text>
</para>
<online.view.item>Notes to Form</online.view.item>
