►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|62|32:59">
<para.text>
If a buyer&ndash;-seller relationship exists between the cooperative and the patron, advance payments will have to be taken into income when received. If the relationship is that of principal and agent, however, the advances may be considered as loans and not taxed until the cooperative, as agent, realizes income for the patron, as principal. The appropriate status cannot be determined from the provisions of the above form; the other terms of the agreement would be needed to make that determination.
</para.text>
</para>
