►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|63|32:60">
<para.text>
Among the many requirements imposed on cooperatives is that of giving notification regarding distributions to the patrons. ►<field>st.ref.id="I05PANJ"</field>26 U.S.C.A. &s;§1388(a)(2). The usual manner of handling this is to incorporate a provision into the bylaws similar to the above and then giving patrons a copy of the bylaw along with the letter of notification described. This must be done before a contract is entered into because, under the Code, the obligation to pay patronage dividends must have existed before the organization received the amount so paid, meaning before the transaction is entered into with the patron.
</para.text>
</para>
►<para ct.id="6d0bf250b92611ef8747b569df12a67d|63|32:60">
<para.text>
The need for the bylaw to which reference is made in this provision arises with respect to qualified written notices of allocation. See ►<field>x.ref.id="I05MHIN"</field>&s;§32:6.
</para.text>
</para>
